quoted.text:
The geographic origins of rapists in Sweden were, at one point, a topic of considerable interest. 

Data on their origins was published in 2021, so we now know where they were from through to 2015.

First: the aggregate. Where were rapists in Sweden born?

The largest group was born outside of Sweden, followed by those born inside Sweden with both parents born in Sweden. 

The former finding doesn't make much sense, since they're such a small part of the population, but the latter does, since they're the overwhelming majority of the population.

So let's look into these slices. 

First up: the 5.7% of rapists born in Sweden with one parent from Sweden. We're going to look at where their parent born outside Sweden was from.

Their dominant source? Other Western Countries.

Now what about the 5.8% of the rapists born in Sweden who had two parents born outside of Sweden?

They were considerably less Western than those with one Swedish-born parent. 

Onto the final and most numerous group: rapists born outside Sweden.

Now that we know their demographics, let's check some other details. Per the paper, we know that 

- 32.5% received social welfare
- 37.3% had low education
- They scored 0.5 d below the mean for resilience
- They scored 0.6 d below the mean for IQ
- They scored 0.95 d below the mean for school achievement
 
In terms of prior convictions, 46.1% had committed a violent crime and 36.8% had committed a property crime. 15.9% had a psychiatric disorder and 19.3% had an alcohol use disorder, while 21% had a drug use disorder.

Their parents were little better: 0.5% of the sample had at least one rapist parent, 16.2% had a white collar criminal parent, 26.4% had a property criminal parent, and 18.6% had a violent criminal as a parent. 24.5% had parents with psychiatric disorders, and 9.4% had parents with histories of drug or alcohol abuse.

With all of that said, the majority of the rapists were still classified as a priori low-risk.

 You can check out the study this data is from here: https://t.co/sPeaBOjtEl
